cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.NE

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper deals with the development of decentralized robust controllers to improve the damping ratios of inter-area oscillation modes in power systems. This falls under the domain of systems and control.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper involves the use of computational techniques to develop the proposed control strategy and to illustrate its effectiveness through case studies. Hence, it can be categorized under computational engineering.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages): The paper does not deal with programming languages explicitly, but it involves the development of control algorithms that can be implemented in software. Hence, it can be categorized under programming languages.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper does not involve the use of AI techniques explicitly, but the proposed control strategy can be seen as a form of intelligent control that adapts to variations in operation conditions and system topology. Hence, it can be categorized under AI.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper does not involve the use of neural or evolutionary computing techniques explicitly, but the proposed control strategy can be seen as a form of adaptive control that adjusts to variations in operation conditions and system topology. Hence, it can be categorized under NE.
